  1676→+## useTrendingProducts Hook (public)
  1677→+
  1678→+```ts
  1679→+type TrendingProductsFetcher = () => Promise<TrendingProduct[]>;
  1680→+
  1681→+type UseTrendingProductsOptions = {
  1682→+  fetcher: TrendingProductsFetcher;
  1683→+  enabled?: boolean;
  1684→+};
  1685→+
  1686→+type UseTrendingProductsResult = {
  1687→+  products: TrendingProduct[];
  1688→+  isLoading: boolean;
  1689→+  isError: boolean;
  1690→+};
  1691→+
  1692→+function useTrendingProducts(options: UseTrendingProductsOptions): UseTrendingProductsResult;
  1693→+```
  1694→+
  1695→+**Implementation notes:**
  1696→+- Dumb hook: calls `fetcher()`, manages `loading`/`error`/`data` state with `useEffect` + `useState`
  1697→+- No React Query, no catalog API wiring — those stay in catalog
  1698→+- No in-memory cache for phase 1 (simple `useEffect`, re-fetches on mount)
  1699→+- `enabled` flag: skip fetch when `false` (matches catalog `useTrendingProducts` pattern)
  1700→+- Returns empty `products: []` on error (same behavior as current catalog hook)
  1701→+
  1702→+**Catalog usage:**
  1703→+```ts
  1704→+// catalog: useTrendingProductsWrapper.js wraps this
  1705→+const { products, isLoading } = useTrendingProducts({
  1706→+  fetcher: () => fetchPromotionalProducts({ categoryId, limit: 20 }),
  1707→+  enabled: true,
  1708→+});
  1709→+```
